3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper deals with improving the performance of AI models, specifically CNNs, in image recognition tasks. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper proposes a technique for regularizing neural networks, which falls under the domain of neural computing. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language): Although the paper does not directly deal with natural language processing, the proposed technique of adding noise to the loss layer could potentially be applied to language models as well, making this category a possibility.
